entry.sense:
waAdK laAx-N, (Aṣ, Ibn-Ma'een, Ḳ,) and laAH-N, (Ḳ,) or this is incorrect, (Ibn-Ma'een,) A valley having intricate defiles, or narrow passes: (Ḳ:) or, abounding with trees, and intricate; 
as also mulotax-N↓: (L:) or, intricate by reason of its trees: (Aṣ:) or it is lAx, without teshdeed, [i. e. laAxN, or, as its derivation presently mentioned implies, laAxK,] (Sh, Ḳ,) from OaloxaI, distorted (L, Ḳ) 
[but in the former written AlxMC] in the mouth. (L.)

