lafaMCN 
Deficiency: (IAth:) raDiytu mina AlwafaMCi biAll-afaMCi [I was content with a deficiency instead of full payment]: 
from a trad. (TA.)

maloquwHapN (IAạr, Ṣ, Ḳ, &c.) and maloquwHN, (IAạr,) which latter is also used in a pl. sense, (Aṣ,) What is in the belly of a she-camel: (AʼObeyd, T, Ṣ, Ḳ, &c.:) or what is in the back of the stallion camel; 
[meaning his progeny in the elemental state;] (Aboo-Saʼeed, Ḳ;) but the former, says Az, is the correct signification: (L:) maloquwHapN is for maloquwHN bihi, converted into a subst., (Mṣb,) from luqiHato, like maHomuwmN from Hum-a, and majonuwnN from jun-a: (Ṣ:) pl. malaAqiyHu. (AʼObeyd, Ṣ, Ḳ, &c.) The Muslims are forbidden to sell malaAqiyH and maDaAmiyn. (L.) 
