5. tly-v 
and lay-ava↓ and luy-iva He (a man, TA,) became like the Benoo-Leyth, or, like a lion, in desire; expl. by SaAra layoviI-a AlhawaI; (Ḳ;) and in zeal in the cause of his party: (TA:) he became like a lion; 
as also Uisotaloyava↓. (L.)
